\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1 \'b7\tab}\pard \fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}
Spaces are usually part of the entry name. Thus, when you specify a dn (distinguished name), do not count on normalization (space stripping).
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1 \'b7\tab}For any field in which a list can be entered (such as values to add, or attributes to display) separate the items using a semi-column and with no spaces.
\par \pard \li720\widctlpar Example:
\par Add entry
\par dn:CN=you,OU=YourUnit,O=YourOrganization,C=US
\par     attribute:description
\par     values   :first description;Second one;Third
\par     attribute:Email-Addresses
\par     values   :you@ms.com;you@msn.com;you@nowhere.nul
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1 \'b7\tab}\pard \fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}
Note that each operation dialog allows you to specify the functions parameters and the different "friends" permutations on the functions. 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1 \'b7\tab}For asynchronous calls, you must use the "Process Pending" entry to see the results of your call.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1 \'b7\tab}Most dialogs are modeless so you can have several dialogs opened at the same time. It is a useful feature\emdash use it.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1 \'b7\tab}\pard \fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}
The primary goal for this utility is to serve as a test tool to aid developers in testing LDAP interfaces. Hence, the UI was compromised for exposing LDAP API as directly as possible. Thus, it is not guaranteed to conform with any UI standards.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f1 \'b7\tab}\pard \fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}Pay attention to the server restrictions and syntax! For instance, in Microsoft\rquote 
s Active Directory, the attribute types of a DN must all be capitalized.
